						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Choḻa, Madiraikoṇḍa Parakēśarivarman, Parāntaka I, Year 34 = 941 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of reclaimed land after purchase by the <hi rend="italic">kanapperumakkaḻ</hi> of Ti[ruttaṇi]yal in Kuṉravattana-kōṭṭam to (the temple of) Tiruvānandapuram for a flower garden. The <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Tiruttaṇiyal seems to have made the land tax-free.</p>						

						</summary>
